{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/keyboardkitpro\/settings-article"]},{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/keyboardkitpro\/settings-article"]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Settings-Article","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Great keyboard apps use the main app to show the current state of the keyboard, if the keyboard is enabled in System Settings, if Full Access is enabled, etc. They can also take users to System Settings to enable the keyboard extension, enable full access, etc."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"KeyboardKit provides tools to make this easier, such as ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Foundation\/URL"},{"type":"text","text":" extensions and custom navigation links."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Keyboard-Settings","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Keyboard Settings"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit has a "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Keyboard\/Settings","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" class that has a global "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Keyboard\/Settings\/store","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" that is used to persist all context settings. If you set up KeyboardKit with a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" that defines an App Group, this store is set up to sync data between the app and its keyboard."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"style":"important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"","type":"text"},{"code":"@AppStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" properties use the store that’s available when they’re first accessed. Make sure to set up a custom store BEFORE accessing any of these settings properties."}]}],"name":"Important","type":"aside"},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"How-to","text":"How to…"},{"level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Sync settings between the app and the keyboard","anchor":"Sync-settings-between-the-app-and-the-keyboard"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"To sync data between the main app and its keyboard, you have to create an App Group and link it to both the app and the keyboard. You can then add the App Group ID to your ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp"},{"text":" and use it to set up your main app and keyboard, as described in ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/App-Article"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can also use "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Keyboard\/Settings\/setupStore(forAppGroup:keyPrefix:)"},{"text":" to set up a store for an App Group, without using a ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardApp"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The main app will always write data to an App Group in a way that is instantly available to the keyboard. A keyboard must however have Full Access enabled for changes to be immediately synced to the app. When Full Access is disabled, the sync will be less reliable."}]}],"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important"},{"text":"Open System Settings","anchor":"Open-System-Settings","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KeyboardKit defines a "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Foundation\/URL\/systemSettings","isActive":true},{"text":" URL that can be used to open your app’s settings screen in System Settings, where users can enable your keyboard, enable Full Access, etc.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can use a standard SwiftUI "},{"code":"Link","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to open this URL from both your app and its keyboard, or trigger a "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardActionHandler\/handle(action:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" with a ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/KeyboardAction\/url(_:id:)","isActive":true},{"text":" action and the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/com.keyboardkit.KeyboardKitPro\/documentation\/KeyboardKitPro\/Foundation\/URL\/systemSettings","type":"reference"},{"text":" URL.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"syntax":"swift","code":["if let url = URL.systemSettings {","    Link(\"Open System Settings\", destination: url)","}"],"type":"codeListing"},{"style":"note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your app randomly navigates to the Settings root instead of your app, try adding an empty settings bundle to your app."}],"type":"paragraph"}],"name":"Note","type":"aside"},{"text":"Integrate with System Settings","anchor":"Integrate-with-System-Settings","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A common feature reque